title: Haydn - Symphonies Nos. 6, 7, 8 - Hogwood, AAM
description:
Haydn: Symphonies Nos. 6, 7, and 8.

Joseph Haydn's Symphonies Nos. 6 (Le matin), 7 (Le midi), and 8 (Le soir), performed by the Academy of Ancient Music under Christopher Hogwood. These symphonies were the first to be written for Prince Esterhazy. They retain features of the old concerto grosso style, so the winds, horns, and strings get many chances at solo passages.

Please enjoy.
